title: For Sale:  WATCH OUT
postcontent:
fella on here is claiming to be selling an "authentic" maadi akm.  he's dead wrong--and probably knows it.  it is a horrific century arms frankenstein rifle called a MISR (made from an egyptian receiver and a MAK90 parts kit).  these rifles are unreliable and of horrible quality.  be careful.  i realize emotions and fear are very high right now, but be sure to educate yourselves before purchasing a firearm.  don't get ripped off.

here's his link:
http://www.armslist.com/posts/1215524/portland-oregon-rifles-for-sale--ak-47-maadi-made-in-egypt

notice in the blurred photo the importer says "C.A.I."  do your research, don't get ripped off.  this is one of those akm rifles that people purposely get rid of after they come across its reputation.

title: For Sale:  Southern Erie Survivalists needed!
postcontent:
Are you preparing yourself? So are we. We are a small group of survivalists who meet and train in the skills needed to mitigate the effects of disaster in our community after a SHTF event.

First off..What we are NOT looking for.
We are not looking for junkies, druggies, felons, anarchists, hippies, drunks, or tactifools.
Just because you saw an episode of doomsday preppers, doesn't mean you are a survivalist.
We are not looking for out of shape, obese, keyboard commandos.
We are not looking for braggers or big mouths. No one cares about you being a survivalist, so why do they need to know?

What we are looking for.
Must be 18 or older.
Healthy, fit individuals who are able to train.
Those who know and understand OPSEC.
Former Military or LE a plus, but not necessary.
People with a relevant skill set.
People with morals.
People who believe in the US Constitution!

So what do we do? We train in prepping/self sufficiency, first aid, marksmanship (Airsoft and live fire drills), bug out drills, disaster response drills (community service/defense).


If this sounds like you and you would like to meet and possibly train with like minded individuals, please respond with an email about yourself. Age, weight, physical abilities, occupation, why you would be an asset to OUR group, etc. Adding a photo will speed up response time.

If you cant submit the info we are requesting...don't bother replying, you will be immediately disqualified.

We are a survivalist/prepper group, interested only in protecting the well being of our families and community.

title: For Sale:  COLT Rattle Snake 1911 24K GOLD 1 OF 1000
postcontent: Up for auction is a beauty of all 1911 pistols I have ever owned. I have only had this piece for about 9 months now I am the first owner I purchased it from the American Historical Foundation in Ashland, Virginia. I honestly regret selling it b/c there are only 1000 of these world wide. I have number 986 I barley made the chance to owning this fine pistol. Of course this is a working firing firearm and it has never been fired before neither handled with humans hands unless with lab gloves were worn first. I honestly never had to handle it anyways until I decided that I have to list it so its only been handled by me with the lab gloves on. Some of the neat features in this pistol are: its a 1911 style, it has real rattlesnake skin grips, its 24 karat Gold in several areas, its displayed in both factory hard colt case and a walnut glass display case with a key to lock the case, its got the Colt Legacy Emblem embedded in the grips, its the colt legacy edition, its got all factory paperwork and documentation/ certificate of authenticity, it also has the factory lock, silicon cleaning towel, white lab gloves, regular factory black rubber grips, and the factory traveling bag used only for traveling and not storing the pistol for a long period of time. This pistol is absolutely beautiful a must have for colt collectors or any collector, you don't find these for sale everyday. Whoever has one of these pistols most likely has it stored away in their safe to past down the family generation, I obviously cant do that I wish I could but I have to move away. I honestly have not seen one of these sold before yet, so they are really hard to come by, but here's your chance to own one now. Enough said the pictures will do the rest of the talking for me and you decide. Definitely bid with confidence on this one, this pistol will always hold its value and rise over the years pass by. I will guarantee you wont find one like the condition this one is in. This is factory new and I am the original owner. Its been a safe queen since the day I bought it. For all bidders please know your state and local laws for owning this piece. This is considered a pistol so legal age is 21.
